The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter 
GWERU City Council Public Relations and Communications officer, Vimbai Chingwaramusee’s star continues to shine after she scooped two accolades at separate events held in Harare. <img class="wp-image-620866 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-58-9.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-58-9.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-58-9-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Gweru City Council (GCC) Chingwaramusee scooped the Women in Public Relations and Communication Effective Communicator in the Public Service entity in Zimbabwe award on Friday. The awards ceremony was organised by the Institute of Public Relations Communications Zimbabwe. On Thursday Chingwaramusee won the Megafest Silver Award Best Female Executive in Zimbabwe 2021. Chingwaramusee said she is delighted that public relations is now being recognised as a key enabler for national economic development. “I am honoured, it shows that the profession of Public Relations is being recognised and appreciated at a national level,” Chungwaramusee said.  “Indeed PR practitioners are an important aspect for national economic development as they create a good brand and image for the nation. So this recognition is of importance to me as I strive to not only brand Gweru but Zimbabwe at large.” Chingwaramusee is a journalist who rose to prominence as a news presenter and current affairs anchor at 984. FM Midlands. She is the board chairperson of Heart of a Woman Trust, a civic society group which is centred on the welfare and rehabilitation of current and ex-female prisoners. Chingwaramusee has won multiple awards since joining Gweru City Council in August 2019. <img class="wp-image-603136 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Untitled-7-11.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Untitled-7-11.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Untitled-7-11-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zimbabwe International Trade Fair (ZITF) Some of the notable accolades include the gold medal won by the Gweru City Council at the Zimbabwe International Trade Fair in 2021 and bronze medal won this year. Chingwaramusee won the CEO’s Network Young PR practitioner award 2021 and she was the Institute of Public Relations Communications Zimbabwe best PR Under 40 in 2020. In all she has won 15 awards of excellence since joining the city council.